tip.text: Laksa broth is supposed to pack a punch of flavours but this delivered only a light slap - flavourful but not "punchy" enough. Compared to the Air Itam laksa, this is milder and less fishy.

The char kuey teow is decently executed (not too salty) but lacking in wok hei. The cockles are small but flavourful (if you prefer big fat juicy cockles, this is not the stall for you) Overall: 3.2/5

tip.text: Char Kuey Teow was incredibly good - the best I ever had in Singapore, it was as good as the above-average ones in Malaysia, and that is really saying something. Prices are on the high side though.
the mixed berries sorbet is sweet but not overpowering, very delicately balanced, well done (:
